metadata.description:
In mythology of ancient Greece, the ruler of the dead and the underworld is the eldest son of "Titan" "Cronus" and "Rhea" In the lottery with his brothers, he won the worst share, and that was the underworld or the world of the dead, while his brothers"Zeus" and "Poseidon" won the sky and the sea, respectively. "Hades" also owned underground mines due to his rule over the underworld and was considered the god of wealth. He kidnapped "Persephone" the daughter of  "Zeus" and "Demeter" from the heavens and brought her to the underworld to rule the underworld with her, but "Zeus" ordered her to release Persephone to relieve her mother "Demeter" gets  
"Damter" when he learns of the incident, becomes so angry that he stops the grains from growing on. So drought is sweeping the world. "Hades" inevitably agrees to bring the girl back, but before he leaves, "Hades" gives her a few pomegranate seeds. "Persephone" does not know that this action will cause him to remain in the underworld forever.
